-- Zimbabwe Sets Minimum Cotton Price of 77 Cents, Herald Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-07-26T09:24:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/zimbabwe-sets-minimum-cotton-price-of-77-cents-herald-reports.html
Zimbabwe’s  Agriculture Ministry  said
cotton farmers must be paid a minimum of 77 cents a kilogram
(2.2 pounds) for their crop, the state-controlled  Herald 
reported, citing Agriculture Minister Joseph Made.  Merchants won’t be permitted to negotiate lower prices with
farmers, the Harare-based Herald reported Made as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at  in Harare
at   blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 